story:
Moonbath carved by light;
Mountains whisper ancient Pause;
Stars cocoon the gods.

Impermanence stirs;
Whispers dance on autumn breeze,
Stealing flight, a leaf.

Silent forest weeps
Sleet caresses dying leaves;
Whispered secrets hush.

Whispers in the breeze;
Leaves of Autumn bid farewell —
Nature's hues transform.

Moon whispers secrets,
To silent, enchanted sea;
Night secrets exchanged.

Whispers in moonlight,
Echoes of dreams intertwine;
Nature's breath exhaled.
